## About

This cheatsheet shows you how to perform an analysis of variance (ANOVA) type test in R where all predictors/explanatory variables are **categorical**. Post-hoc tests and reporting of results are also covered in this cheatsheet.


## ANOVAs as general linear models (GLMs)

All ANOVA models in this cheatsheet will use the `lm()` function to fit a linear model first, and then use the `Anova()` function from the `car` package to perform the ANOVA test. The `Anova()` function is used because it provides more options for unbalanced designs and interactions between factors.

Run the follwing code to install all required packages:



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
if (!require("Require")) install.packages("Require")
Require::Require(car, emmeans, gt, gtsummary)
```
